.TH simple_shell 1 "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a minimal Unix shell implemented in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [command [arguments] ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimal Unix command interpreter written in C that reproduces the behavior of
.BR /bin/sh .

It allows executing Unix commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

The shell supports:
.IP \[bu] 2
Executing programs using .BR execve (2)
.IP \[bu] 2
Interactive mode with a prompt displayed (.B $)
.IP \[bu] 2
Non-interactive mode (reading commands from a pipe or a file)
.IP \[bu] 2
Built-in commands: .B exit , .B env
.IP \[bu] 2
Automatic searching for commands in directories listed in the .B PATH variable

.SH USAGE

.TP
.B ./hsh
Starts the shell in interactive mode (displays the prompt \fB$\fR and waits for user commands).

.TP
.B echo "ls" | ./hsh
Runs the shell in non-interactive mode, reading commands from standard input.

.TP
.B /bin/ls
Executes a command using its absolute path.

.TP
.B ls -l
Executes a command with arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns:
.IP \[bu] 2
0 on success
.IP \[bu] 2
127 if the command is not found
.IP \[bu] 2
The exit status of the executed command otherwise

